sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Browser as Browser
    participant Client as App Cliente
    participant Auth as Registration /auth
    participant Token as /api/auth/token
    participant TenantDb as tenant_{id}
    participant Master as SaasMasterDb

    Note over Browser,Auth: Não há resolução Host -> Tenant no código atual.
    Note over Browser,Auth: O app informa tenant_id explicitamente no início do SSO.

    Client->>Client: Selecionar tenantId conhecido
    Client->>Browser: Redirect /auth/login?tenant_id={tenantId}&client_id={clientId}&...
    Browser->>Auth: GET /auth/login com tenant_id
    Auth->>TenantDb: Buscar OAuthClient do tenant informado
    Auth->>Auth: Validar redirect_uri, scope, state, nonce e PKCE S256
    Auth->>Master: Criar HostedAuthTransaction e HostedAuthSession
    Auth-->>Browser: Login hospedado, ou reuso de lc_sso do mesmo tenant
    Browser->>Auth: POST credenciais e 2FA quando necessário
    Auth->>Master: Criar/reutilizar SsoSession vinculada ao TenantId
    Auth-->>Browser: 302 redirect_uri?code&state
    Browser->>Client: Entregar code e state
    Client->>Token: POST /api/auth/token com X-Tenant-Id e code_verifier
    Token->>Master: Consumir AuthorizationCodeGrant vinculado ao tenant
    Token->>TenantDb: Recarregar usuário/status/roles
    Token-->>Client: access_token tenant-scoped + refresh_token

    Note over Client,Token: Futuro Custom Domains deve substituir tenant explícito por contexto server-side somente depois de existir código correspondente.
